# Cursor Context Map

- Put short, always-on constraints in rules.
- Put specialized multi-step workflows in `.cursor/skills`.
- Use `.cursor/agents` only for parallel specialist work with a narrow responsibility.
- Keep hooks lightweight; use them for reminders or guardrails, not destructive automation.
- Keep `.cursor/mcp.json` for real external systems only. Do not add placeholder remote servers that the project does not use.
- Avoid duplicating the same guidance across `AGENTS.md`, rules, and skills.
